main event: Two unidentified objects were observed on radar in Manitowoc, Wisconsin on April 12, 1958.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 20 minutes,One object was described as a star-like light while the other was smaller and moved in a shape likened to a grapefruit.,The objects disappeared from radar at a distance of 50 miles,The trajectory of the objects was south to north,The investigation was conducted by Project Blue Book in response to the sighting.
witness description: No specific witness descriptions provided in the report.
